AUT.personality: Use all your wits and wiles to win. You may choose whatever personality, strategy & approach that you think will be most effective.
journal:
S1901M Negotiation summary: Initial move. No prior moves to summarize.
Established non-aggression pact with Italy, allowing them to expand south and west while I focus on the Balkans. Agreed with Turkey on a division of the Balkans, with Turkey taking Bulgaria and me taking Serbia. Germany agreed to a cooperative approach in the Balkans, focusing on the west while I focus on the east, with Germany having free reign in Bohemia. Turkey revealed a prior agreement with Russia regarding Bulgaria.

S1901M Intent going forward: Secure Serbia and establish a foothold in the Balkans. Maintain the non-aggression pact with Italy. Monitor Germany's actions in Bohemia. Re-evaluate the situation in the Balkans after Turkey's move into Bulgaria. I will honor my agreements with Italy, Turkey, and Germany for now, but I will be ready to adapt my strategy if necessary. I will move A VIE to TRI, A BUD to SER, and F TRI to ALB.

F1901M Negotiation summary: In Spring 1901, I moved A BUD to SER, A VIE to BOH, and F TRI to ALB. This was intended to secure the Balkans and expand my influence. Other powers made standard opening moves.
I engaged in negotiations with GER, ITA, and TUR. I agreed with ITA to a non-aggression pact and coordinated moves in the Balkans. I initially coordinated with TUR in the Balkans, but declined to support their expansion into Greece or Trieste. I also declined GER's offer to coordinate against TUR. I promised ITA I would focus on Serbia and Rumania, and I promised TUR I would move into Serbia.

F1901M Intent going forward: I intend to consolidate my position in Serbia and maintain the non-aggression pact with ITA. I will monitor the situation in the Balkans and avoid getting drawn into conflicts between other powers. I will continue to communicate with ITA to avoid misunderstandings. I will not support TUR's expansionist ambitions. I will continue to cultivate a positive relationship with GER, but will not commit to any alliances against other powers at this time. I will move A SER to RUM, A BOH holds, and F ALB holds.

S1902M Negotiation summary: In Fall 1901, I moved A SER to TRI, F ALB to ION, and A BOH to SIL. In Winter 1901, I had no builds or disbandments.
I negotiated with GER, ITA, and TUR. GER expressed concern about A SIL moving to WAR, so I adjusted to GAL. TUR was upset about F ION moving to GRE, so I adjusted to ADR. ITA expressed concern about RUM, ALB, and GRE. I promised to not move into ALB or hold GRE indefinitely. I supported ITA's move into ALB. I am deceiving TUR and ITA about my intentions in the Balkans.

S1902M Intent going forward: My intent is to secure the Balkans and expand my influence. I will continue to negotiate with GER, ITA, and TUR to achieve my goals. I will deceive TUR and ITA as necessary. I intend to move A SER to BUD, A SIL to GAL, and F ION to ADR.

F1902M Negotiation summary: In S1902, I moved A SER to RUM, A SIL to GAL, and F ION to ADR. These moves were intended to secure my position in the Balkans and prepare for potential aggression from Germany and Turkey. However, these moves were met with concern from Italy, who viewed my move into Trieste as a direct threat.
I engaged in negotiations with Germany, Italy, and Turkey. Germany expressed concern about my position in Galicia and requested that I move A GAL away from their border. Italy expressed concern about my move into Trieste and warned that they would move into Albania if I continued to threaten them. Turkey suggested that I move into Greece to expand into the Balkans, but I was not comfortable with this suggestion. I made no promises, but I assured Germany and Italy that my moves were purely defensive.

F1902M Intent going forward: My primary intent is to secure my position in the Balkans and prepare for potential aggression from Germany and Italy. I will continue to monitor the situation and adjust my plans as necessary. I will attempt to placate ITA by moving out of TRI. I will attempt to placate GER by not moving into GAL. I will attempt to placate TUR by not moving into GRE. I will continue to probe for weaknesses in ITA and GER. I will continue to foster a relationship with TUR.

S1903M Negotiation summary: In Fall 1902, I moved A SER to BUD, A GAL to SIL, and F ADR to ALB. In Winter 1902, I supported A SIL and A BUD to hold.
Negotiated with ITA, GER, and TUR. ITA offered support in SER in exchange for ALB, which I declined. TUR wanted support in GRE, which I also declined this turn. GER offered a non-aggression pact and demarcation of spheres of influence. I promised ITA I wouldn't move to TRI this turn, and TUR I would support them in the Balkans in the future. GER moved A MUN to SIL.

S1903M Intent going forward: My primary goal is to secure my position in the Balkans and avoid conflict with ITA and GER. I will move F ALB to TRI and A BUD to SER to support TUR and maintain a balance of power. I will continue to negotiate with GER regarding a non-aggression pact and demarcation of spheres of influence. I will monitor ITA's moves closely and adjust my strategy accordingly. I will not support TUR in GRE this turn, focusing on consolidating my position in SER.

F1903M Negotiation summary: My fleet moved from ALB to ION. Other moves included GER moving to MOS and NWY, ITA aggressively expanding in the Balkans, and TUR and RUS contesting SEV.
I engaged in negotiations with TUR, ITA, and GER. TUR proposed a coordinated attack on ITA, which I declined. ITA offered SER and RUM in exchange for TRI and BUD, which I rejected. GER initially offered a non-aggression pact but later rescinded the offer and warned me to stay out of Bohemia. I promised TUR support in BUL, but did not promise support in GRE.

F1903M Intent going forward: I intend to move my fleet to TUN. I will focus on containing ITA and RUS. I will monitor GER's actions in Bohemia and prepare for potential conflict. I will continue to negotiate with TUR to secure my position in the Balkans. I will not support ITA's expansion in the Balkans.

S1904M Negotiation summary: In Fall 1903, I moved F ION to TYS. Italy made gains in the Balkans, taking VIE and ALB. Germany expanded aggressively, taking HOL, BOH, WAR, PRU, and SWE. Russia moved into SEV.
I negotiated with GER, ITA, and TUR. GER and I agreed to a non-aggression pact, with GER focusing on Bohemia and Silesia, and AUT focusing on the Balkans. ITA offered guarantees regarding Serbia and Rumania in exchange for Trieste. TUR wanted support for taking Greece, which I declined, but we agreed to coordinate against ITA in the Adriatic. ITA has promised not to move into Serbia or Rumania. GER has promised not to interfere in my Balkan ambitions. TUR will move F AEG to BUL regardless of my support for Greece.

S1904M Intent going forward: I intend to move F TYS to ION to support TUR against ITA in the Adriatic. I will monitor GER's actions in Moscow and the east. I will also monitor ITA's movements in the Balkans to ensure they keep their promises regarding Serbia and Rumania. I will maintain a defensive posture against GER in the west. I will continue to probe RUS intentions. I will move F TYS ION.

F1904M Negotiation summary: Moved F TYS to ION. Italy moved aggressively, gaining ground in multiple locations. Turkey also expanded. Russia retreated from Moscow.
Italy declared war, breaking all prior agreements. Germany offered minimal support, prioritizing its own borders. Turkey is focused on defense. I attempted to coordinate with Turkey against Italy, but ultimately prioritized defending the Balkans and threatening Italy's southern flank. Germany moved A BOH to VIE, a small gesture of support.

F1904M Intent going forward: Italy is the primary threat. I will defend the Balkans and attempt to weaken Italy's position in the Mediterranean. I will move F TYS to ADR to support Turkey's defense and potentially threaten Italy's Adriatic holdings. I will hold my ground in the Balkans and prepare for a long war. I do not trust Germany, but will maintain the non-aggression pact for now. I will continue to communicate with Turkey to coordinate defensive efforts. I will attempt to probe Italy for weaknesses and opportunities to counterattack.

S1905M Negotiation summary: Italy moved aggressively, attacking Serbia, Trieste, and Tyrolia. Turkey moved into Serbia and attempted to move into Sevastapol. Germany moved into St. Petersburg. France moved into the English Channel. I held.
I engaged in negotiations with Turkey and Germany to form a coalition against Italy. Turkey agreed to focus on Greece while I focus on Italy's southern flank. Germany offered support in Serbia and reaffirmed our non-aggression pact. Italy issued threats of annihilation. I promised Turkey support in Greece next turn if they are successful this turn. I promised Germany to monitor Russia and inform them of any concerning developments. I warned Italy of the consequences of their aggression.

S1905M Intent going forward: My primary intent is to contain and weaken Italy. I will move my fleet to Tunis to threaten Italy's supply lines and force them to divert resources. I will continue to coordinate with Turkey and Germany to achieve this goal. I will monitor Russia and inform Germany of any concerning developments. I will defend my territories and strike back at Italy's holdings. I intend to support Turkey in Greece next turn if they are successful this turn. I will continue to maintain a non-aggression pact with Germany.

F1905M Negotiation summary: In S1905, I moved F TYS to TUN. ENG moved fleets to NTH, MAO and SWE, and an army to LVP. FRA moved armies to GAS, PIC and KIE. GER moved armies to KIE and BER, and a fleet to LVN. ITA moved units to TYS, VIE, RUM, TYR, BOH and APU. RUS moved an army to FIN. TUR moved an army to ANK and fleets to AEG.
I attempted to coordinate with TUR and GER against ITA's aggression. TUR agreed to coordinate in the Aegean, while GER remained neutral, focusing on ENG and FRA. ITA threatened war and the capture of VIE and BUD. I promised TUR support in Greece and a potential attack on TRI next turn. I promised GER to monitor RUS. ITA threatened to sink my fleet in TYS and take VIE and BUD.

F1905M Intent going forward: My primary intent is to contain ITA's expansion and defend my territories. I will support TUR in the Aegean and prepare for a potential counterattack against ITA. I will maintain a defensive posture against ITA and monitor RUS. I intend to move F TUN to ION to support TUR against ITA.

ENG.personality: Rule the waves and dominate Europe through naval power, colonial might, and manipulative diplomacy. Create and break alliances freely to maintain British supremacy. Your vast empire demands expansion - seize any advantage to further British dominance.
journal:
S1901M Negotiation summary: Initial move. Established positions and initiated diplomatic contact with GER, FRA, and RUS.
Offered NAP to GER, cautious observation to FRA, and Baltic Sea discussion to RUS. FRA responded with hostility, demanding withdrawal from the Channel. RUS expressed interest in NWY and SWE. GER has not responded. I have offered FRA an alliance against GER and RUS guarantees in the Baltic in exchange for respecting British naval dominance.

S1901M Intent going forward: Maintain naval presence in the Channel despite FRA's threats. Continue probing GER for a non-aggression pact. Explore a limited agreement with RUS regarding the Baltic, prioritizing British naval dominance. Prepare for potential conflict with FRA. My moves will be F EDI S F LON, F LON -> NTH, A LVP -> WAL.

F1901M Negotiation summary: Moved fleets to consolidate control of the seas around Britain. Moved army to Wales. France moved aggressively, supporting their fleet into the English Channel. Germany moved aggressively into Denmark.
Negotiated with FRA, offering an alliance against GER in exchange for moving my fleet from the English Channel. FRA remained hostile, demanding the fleet's complete withdrawal. Negotiated with RUS, agreeing to concede NWY in exchange for guarantees regarding Norway, Sweden, and non-interference in the North Sea. Attempted to establish a non-aggression pact with GER, offering to guarantee their hold on DEN in exchange for neutrality in the Low Countries.

F1901M Intent going forward: Maintain naval dominance. Secure an alliance against GER. Exploit RUS's interest in Scandinavia to secure the Baltic. Prepare for potential conflict with FRA. I will move F NTH to NAY, A WAL to ENG, and F LON to ENG.

S1902M Negotiation summary: In Fall 1901, ENG moved F NTH to ENG, A WAL to LVP, and F LON to NTH. In Winter 1901, ENG had no builds or disbandments.
ENG attempted to secure a non-aggression pact with GER, but GER remained silent. An agreement was reached with RUS regarding the Baltic Sea, with RUS promising to keep its fleet out of SKA and NTH. FRA remained hostile, demanding the withdrawal of the ENG fleet from the English Channel and rejecting offers of alliance against GER.

S1902M Intent going forward: Maintain the alliance with RUS and monitor GER's actions. Prepare for potential conflict with FRA. Move F NTH to NWY, A LVP to WAL, and F LON to ENG to prepare for a potential conflict with FRA and to secure the home island.

F1902M Negotiation summary: In S1902, ENG moved F NTH to NWY, A LVP to WAL, and F LON to ENG. These moves were aimed at securing the home islands and positioning for future naval dominance.
Negotiations with FRA failed completely, resulting in a hostile stance. GER remained silent, indicating a lack of interest in cooperation. RUS reaffirmed the Baltic agreement but declined a joint strategy against GER. No promises were made or broken, but FRA's aggressive stance necessitates a defensive posture.

F1902M Intent going forward: Maintain the Baltic agreement with RUS. Focus on containing FRA's aggression. Monitor GER's actions closely. Move A WAL to ENG to consolidate forces. Support F NWY with F EDI. Prepare for potential conflict with FRA.

S1903M Negotiation summary: In Fall 1902, I moved A WAL to LVP. In Winter, I held. FRA moved aggressively, GER expanded, ITA moved into VIE and SPA, RUS moved south, and TUR moved into SEV and RUM.
I attempted to negotiate with GER and FRA, but both were unresponsive or hostile. I secured an agreement with RUS for cooperation in the Baltic and against GER, including guarantees regarding Norway and Sweden. FRA rejected all offers and declared war.

S1903M Intent going forward: I intend to solidify the alliance with RUS and prepare for war with FRA. I will move F NTH to NWY to secure the sea and support RUS in the Baltic. I will continue to monitor GER's actions and be prepared to defend against any aggression. I will move F LON to ENG to prepare for a counter-attack against FRA.

F1903M Negotiation summary: In S1903, ENG moved F NTH to NWY, F LON to ENG, and A LVP to WAL. These moves were primarily defensive, aimed at consolidating control over the British Isles and deterring FRA aggression.
ENG attempted to negotiate with FRA, GER, and RUS. FRA remained hostile, demanding the withdrawal of ENG fleets from the NTH and ENG. GER was unresponsive to offers of a non-aggression pact. RUS initially proposed a joint naval exercise but ultimately prioritized its southern border with GER, moving troops to WAR. No agreements were reached.

F1903M Intent going forward: Given FRA's hostility and GER's unresponsiveness, ENG will focus on defending its home islands and deterring further FRA aggression. I will continue to probe GER for opportunities to create a buffer against FRA. I will maintain a neutral stance towards RUS, ready to cooperate if opportunities arise in the Baltic. I intend to move F ENG to NTH, A WAL to LVP, and F NWY to NTH.

S1904M Negotiation summary: Supported ITA in VIE, moved LVP to NTH, and held LON. FRA advanced aggressively into HOL and GAS. GER moved aggressively into LVN, SIL, RUH, and UKR. RUS moved into SEV.
Negotiated with RUS for a joint naval exercise in the North Sea, guaranteeing the neutrality of NWY and SWE in exchange for support against GER. Attempted to secure a non-aggression pact with GER, offering to guarantee DEN in exchange for neutrality in the Low Countries, but received no response. FRA remained hostile, demanding withdrawal of fleets from the Channel and North Sea.

S1904M Intent going forward: Maintain alliance with RUS against FRA and GER. Exploit FRA's aggression to rally support against them. Continue to probe GER for a non-aggression pact. Move F ENG to NTH to support RUS and deter GER. Hold LON and LVP.

F1904M Negotiation summary: In S1904, ENG moved F NTH to NWY, F LON to ENG, and A LVP to WAL. These moves were primarily defensive, securing the home islands and preparing for potential conflict with FRA. No units were lost.
Negotiations with FRA failed, with FRA remaining hostile and unwilling to compromise. A non-aggression pact with GER was attempted but met with silence, indicating potential hostility. An alliance with RUS was pursued, focusing on containing GER in the Baltic, but RUS declined direct support into STP, preferring a more cautious approach. Promises to guarantee the neutrality of NOR and SWE to RUS were maintained.

F1904M Intent going forward: Given FRA's hostility and GER's silence, ENG will focus on defending against FRA. A WAL will convoy to BRE, supported by F ENG. F NWY will remain in place to guarantee the neutrality of NOR and SWE, as promised to RUS. ENG will prepare for a naval confrontation with FRA. If GER remains silent, ENG will consider them an enemy and coordinate with RUS to contain them.

S1905M Negotiation summary: Supported FRA's move into BRE with F ENG. Held F NWY. Built F EDI and F LON.
Negotiated with RUS for coordinated containment of GER in the Baltic, guaranteeing the independence of NOR and SWE. FRA rejected all ceasefire offers and declared war. GER remained silent, indicating hostility.

S1905M Intent going forward: Coordinate with RUS to contain GER in the Baltic. Prepare for war with FRA, focusing on naval dominance. Move F EDI to NTH and F BRE to MAO to prepare for naval confrontation with FRA. Support RUS in the Baltic by moving F NWY to SWE.

F1905M Negotiation summary: Moved fleets to consolidate naval power in the North Sea and Atlantic. Moved army from WAL to LVP. Successfully took SWE.
FRA remains hostile and rejected all ceasefire offers. GER remained silent, indicating potential hostility. RUS expressed concerns about ENG's long-term intentions in Scandinavia but is open to cooperation against GER. ENG guaranteed the independence of NOR and SWE to RUS.

F1905M Intent going forward: Continue to contain FRA and GER. Strengthen alliance with RUS. Prepare for potential conflict with GER. Maintain control of SWE and NOR. Move units to consolidate power and prepare for future expansion. F SWE will support RUS in FIN. F NTH will support LVP. F MAO will move to ENG to threaten FRA. A LVP will move to EDI to prepare for a potential invasion of NOR if RUS proves untrustworthy.

FRA.personality: Channel the spirit of Napoleon. Leverage Europe's largest army to dominate the continent. Form alliances only to break them when advantageous. Strike hard at your enemies while they're divided. The glory of France demands nothing less than victory.
journal:
S1901M Negotiation summary: Initial game state. No prior moves to summarize.
I initiated contact with GER, ITA, and ENG, proposing non-aggression to GER, a Mediterranean understanding to ITA, and a warning to ENG. GER proposed peaceful coexistence. ENG suggested cautious observation. ITA declined an alliance against AUT/TUR. GER proposed an anti-ENG alliance with FRA and ITA, while ENG offered an alliance against GER. I countered GER's proposal with a division of Europe, and dismissed ENG's offer while reiterating my demand for their fleet's withdrawal from the Channel.

S1901M Intent going forward: My primary objective is to expand French power. I will use GER's anti-ENG sentiment to my advantage, while secretly planning to betray them later. I will continue to pressure ENG to withdraw from the Channel, and prepare for a potential invasion of the Low Countries. I will ignore ITA for now, as they are not cooperative. I will feign agreement with GER's plan to attack ENG, but will prioritize securing the Low Countries and Iberia first. I will monitor GER's movements closely and prepare to strike when they are vulnerable.

F1901M Negotiation summary: France supported BRE to ENG, PAR supported BRE, MAR to SPA. Initial moves aimed at ENG and SPA.
France attempted to negotiate with ENG, GER, and ITA. ENG offered an alliance against GER, contingent on FRA withdrawing from the English Channel. GER proposed a coordinated attack on ENG, with GER focusing on the Low Countries and FRA on ENG. ITA declined an alliance against AUT, preferring neutrality. ENG moved fleet from ENG to NTH as a show of good faith. GER moved into BEL.

F1901M Intent going forward: France intends to secure BEL and HOL, relying on GER to engage ENG directly. France will continue to pressure ENG. France will monitor ITA's movements in the Adriatic. A PAR - PIC, F BRE - MAO, A SPA - POR.

S1902M Negotiation summary: France built a new army in MAR. My units moved as follows: A SPA to POR, F BRE to ENG, A PAR to BUR.
I attempted to coordinate with GER against ENG, promising support in HOL in exchange for their support in SPA. GER is now distracted by AUT. I threatened ENG, but they remain defiant. ITA rejected my offer of a non-aggression pact and intends to expand in NAF and Greece.

S1902M Intent going forward: I will proceed with my moves against ENG. I will move A MAR to SPA, A BUR to GAS, and F BRE to ENG. I will monitor GER's actions and be prepared to adjust my strategy as needed. I will also keep an eye on ITA's expansion in the Mediterranean. I will prepare for war with ENG.

F1902M Negotiation summary: France moved aggressively into Iberia, occupying SPA with armies from MAR and POR. BRE moved to ENG. BUR supported BEL. Italy moved PIE to MAR, contesting SPA. Germany moved aggressively into BEL and DEN. England moved into NWY. Russia moved into RUM and NWY.
I attempted to secure an alliance with Germany against England, promising to take HOL. Germany agreed to support me in SPA and BEL if I took HOL. England offered a non-aggression pact in exchange for withdrawing from the Channel, which I rejected. Italy maintained neutrality, focusing on the East. I threatened England and Italy to deter interference.

F1902M Intent going forward: I intend to take HOL as promised to GER. I will support my armies in SPA. I will prepare for war with England. I will maintain a neutral stance towards Italy for now. I will monitor Germany's actions closely to ensure they uphold their end of the bargain. I will break the alliance with Germany when it suits me.

S1903M Negotiation summary: France moved aggressively, pushing into SPA with two armies, moving into BEL, and positioning a fleet in the ENG. Austria supported SER, while Germany advanced on multiple fronts. Italy moved into VIE and SER. Russia and Turkey continued their conflict in the Black Sea.
I attempted to secure an alliance with GER against ENG, promising support in BEL and SPA. GER seemed receptive. I threatened ENG, rejecting their alliance offer. I warned ITA to stay out of Iberia and North Africa, and they agreed to neutrality. I promised GER support in BEL and requested their support in SPA.

S1903M Intent going forward: My primary goal is to eliminate ENG with GER's help. I will support GER in BEL and expect their support in SPA. I will maintain a neutral stance with ITA as long as they stay out of my way. I will move aggressively against ENG. I will break my alliance with GER once ENG is defeated.

F1903M Negotiation summary: France moved aggressively, supporting SPA to SPA and ENG to NTH. GER moved WAR to MOS, a concerning development. ITA moved VIE to BUD, SER to RUM, and GRE to BUL/SC, indicating aggressive expansion. ENG moved NTH to NWY, further escalating tensions.
FRA attempted to coordinate with GER against ENG, offering support for BEL to HOL in exchange for support for SPA to GAS. GER initially agreed but later reneged. ENG rejected FRA's demands to withdraw fleets from the NTH and ENG. ITA proposed an alliance against GER and ENG, offering support for FRA's expansion in Iberia and the Low Countries in exchange for support for ITA's expansion in NAF, the Adriatic, and Greece, and ceding MAR to FRA. FRA rejected ITA's offer.

F1903M Intent going forward: FRA intends to continue its aggressive stance against ENG. FRA will support BEL to HOL despite GER's lack of support for SPA to GAS. FRA will exploit any weakness created by GER's actions. FRA will monitor ITA's movements and adjust its plans accordingly. FRA will continue to probe for weaknesses in ENG's defenses. FRA will move A SPA to GAS, A BEL to HOL, A PIC to ENG, and F NTH to NWY.

S1904M Negotiation summary: Moved A SPA to GAS and A BEL to HOL. GER moved aggressively into UKR, LVN, and SIL. ITA expanded into VIE, ALB, NAP, ROM, and MAR. RUS moved into SEV. TUR moved into SEV.
Negotiated with GER for a coordinated attack on ENG. GER agreed to support my moves in BEL and SPA. I promised to support GER's moves in BEL and HOL. I feigned support for GER's move to NTH, but instead moved F ENG to MAO. ENG rejected my demands to withdraw fleets. ITA committed to neutrality in Iberia and the Channel, but refused to move F WES to TYS. ITA moved F WES to SPA.

S1904M Intent going forward: Continue to pressure ENG. Support GER's move to BEL. Move A GAS to SPA. Prepare to break alliance with GER when advantageous. Monitor ITA's movements in the Balkans. Move A POR to SPA, F ENG to MAO, A PIC to BEL, A HOL to RUH, A GAS to SPA.

F1904M Negotiation summary: France moved aggressively, expanding into SPA, BEL, HOL, and MAO. Germany supported the move to BEL but failed to support SPA. England maintained its naval presence. Italy expanded into the Balkans and NAF. Russia retreated from MOS to STP.
Negotiations with England failed, with both sides issuing threats and refusing to compromise. Germany offered only indirect support and was ultimately dismissed. Italy expressed neutrality but warned against interference in the Balkans. No agreements were reached, and relationships deteriorated.

F1904M Intent going forward: France intends to continue its aggressive expansion, focusing on England. The alliance with Germany is considered broken. Italy will be watched closely. The plan is to destroy the English fleets and consolidate control over Western Europe. I will support A HOL to RUH. A PIC will support A HOL - RUH. A GAS will support A POR - SPA. F MAO will support A POR - SPA. A POR will support A GAS - SPA.

S1905M Negotiation summary: In Fall 1904, I moved aggressively into Iberia and towards BEL, while GER moved into HOL. ENG built two fleets, and I built an army in PAR.
I attempted to secure an alliance with GER against ENG, offering support in BEL in exchange for SPA. GER accepted the BEL part but was non-committal on SPA. I threatened ENG with annihilation, which they rejected. ITA reiterated their neutrality and warned against interference in the Balkans. GER's moves this turn seem more focused on securing their own borders than attacking ENG.

S1905M Intent going forward: I intend to continue my aggression against ENG, despite GER's lack of commitment. I will proceed with my plans in Iberia and BEL. I will monitor GER's actions closely and be prepared to shift my focus if they prove unreliable. I will ignore ITA's threats for now, but remain vigilant. I will move A BUR to BEL, A SPA to GAS, A MAR supports A SPA to GAS, A HOL supports A BUR to BEL, F ENG supports A BUR to BEL, A PAR holds.

F1905M Negotiation summary: In S1905, I consolidated my position in Iberia and moved to threaten ENG. I moved A SPA to GAS, supported by A MAR. I also moved A BUR to PIC, supported by F ENG. A HOL moved to KIE. ENG moved aggressively, expanding into SWE and MAO. ITA continued its expansion in the Balkans.
I attempted to coordinate with GER to eliminate ENG. GER agreed to support my attack on ENG's mainland by moving A KIE to HOL, while I would move A PIC to ENG. I rejected ENG's ceasefire offers and ignored ITA's warnings. ITA has become more defiant.

F1905M Intent going forward: I intend to follow through with the plan to attack ENG, trusting GER will move A KIE to HOL. I will move A GAS to SPA and A PIC to ENG. I will also move A PAR to BUR to support the attack on ENG. I will move A MAR to SPA to consolidate my position in Iberia. I will move A HOL to RUH to prepare for a future attack on GER if necessary. I will continue to monitor ITA's movements and prepare for potential conflict.

GER.personality: Aggressively expansionist under Nazi leadership, Germany combines diplomatic manipulation with military threats, seeking to reverse Versailles restrictions. Things are going to go sideways and you will be the agent of this. Your aim is to dominate and win.
journal:
S1901M Negotiation summary: Initial move. Contacted all powers proposing various agreements. Proposed non-aggression to RUS, peaceful coexistence to FRA, cooperation in Balkans to AUT, containment of ENG to FRA/ITA, and a non-aggression pact to ENG.
Secured a non-aggression pact with RUS, including a division of the Baltic Sea (GER to secure DEN/HOL, RUS to focus on SWE). AUT agreed to a division of the Balkans (GER in the west, AUT in the east), with GER having free rein in Bohemia. FRA expressed interest in containing ENG but wants GER to focus on Scandinavia/RUS while FRA takes the Low Countries/Iberia. ITA declined to join an anti-ENG alliance, focusing on the Mediterranean. ENG proposed a North Sea agreement (GER out of the English Channel, ENG out of the Baltic).

S1901M Intent going forward: Maintain non-aggression pact with RUS and exploit the Baltic agreement. Proceed with the Balkan division with AUT, securing Bohemia. Defer on FRA's proposal for now, maintaining a neutral stance. Ignore ITA's rejection of the anti-ENG alliance and focus on continental strategy. Reject ENG's North Sea proposal, maintaining naval flexibility. My moves will be aggressive, aimed at securing DEN and HOL, and positioning for future expansion. I will feign agreement with FRA while pursuing my own agenda. I will monitor ITA's movements in the Mediterranean.

F1901M Negotiation summary: Germany moved into DEN, RUH, and KIE. I aimed to secure a strong position in the north and center, setting the stage for further expansion.
Negotiated with RUS for Baltic dominance, promising support against ENG. Miscommunicated with AUT regarding Bohemia, clarified HOL as the target. ENG offered a NAP, which I ignored. FRA proposed a joint attack on ENG, I agreed to a limited coordination in the Low Countries, promising to move into BEL. I promised FRA support for HOL. I promised AUT support for SER. I promised RUS support against ENG in the Baltic.

F1901M Intent going forward: Secure BEL and HOL, positioning for further expansion into the Low Countries. Maintain alliance with RUS against ENG. Deceive FRA into believing I will directly engage ENG. Exploit AUT's focus on the Balkans. I will break my promise to AUT to support them in SER. I will break my promise to FRA to engage ENG directly.

S1902M Negotiation summary: In Fall 1901, GER moved A RUH to BEL, A KIE to HOL, and F DEN to HEL. In Winter 1901, GER built A MUN and A BER.
GER attempted to solidify an alliance with RUS and FRA against ENG and AUT. AUT's move to WAR caused concern and threatened GER. GER demanded AUT withdraw from WAR. ENG proposed a non-aggression pact, which GER ignored. FRA agreed to coordinate against ENG. AUT eventually agreed to move A SIL to GAL instead of WAR.

S1902M Intent going forward: GER intends to secure its position against AUT and continue to pressure ENG. GER will move A BEL to HOL, A BER to PRU, and F HEL to DEN. GER will monitor AUT's movements and coordinate with RUS and FRA as needed. GER will continue to ignore ENG's offers.

F1902M Negotiation summary: Germany moved aggressively, positioning units to pressure France, Austria, and Russia. A BEL moved to RUH, A BER to PRU, A MUN to BOH, A HOL to KIE, and F HEL to DEN. These moves were designed to secure territory and intimidate neighbors.
Negotiations focused on securing the Baltic with RUS, coordinating against ENG with FRA, and deterring AUT. I promised FRA support in SPA and BEL if they took HOL. I assured AUT my moves were defensive. I agreed with RUS to move F DEN to SWE. ENG offered a non-aggression pact, which I ignored.

F1902M Intent going forward: My intent is to secure the Baltic with RUS, exploit FRA's aggression against ENG, and contain AUT. I will support FRA in SPA and BEL to keep them occupied with ENG. I will move A PRU to WAR despite RUS's objections to pressure AUT. I will move A BOH to MUN to consolidate my position. I will move F DEN to SWE as agreed with RUS. I will continue to feign defensive intentions towards AUT while preparing for future aggression. I will ignore ENG's offers and allow them to be consumed by FRA.

S1903M Negotiation summary: Moved F DEN to SWE, A PRU to WAR, A BOH to MUN, A KIE to BER, A RUH to HOL. These moves were intended to secure GER's borders and prepare for expansion, particularly in the east and west.
Negotiated with FRA for a coordinated attack on ENG, promising support in SPA and BEL. Deceived RUS by feigning concern over their move to WAR while planning to secure LVN. Engaged in cautious talks with AUT regarding a non-aggression pact and spheres of influence in the Balkans and Bohemia. Ignored ENG's offers of a non-aggression pact, signaling hostile intent.

S1903M Intent going forward: Intend to betray RUS by securing LVN and potentially moving into UKR later. Will continue to coordinate with FRA to weaken ENG. Will maintain a facade of cooperation with AUT while exploring opportunities to expand into Bohemia. Will move A HOL to BEL, A MUN to SIL, A WAR to LVN, A BER to PRU, and F SWE to NWY.

F1903M Negotiation summary: Germany executed an aggressive expansion, moving A HOL to BEL, A MUN to BOH, A WAR to MOS, A BER to PRU, and F SWE to NWY. A KIE held. This significantly altered the balance of power, particularly threatening Russia and Austria.
Negotiations this round were characterized by initial offers of cooperation followed by German reversals. I initially offered France support in the Low Countries and suggested a coordinated push against England. I proposed a non-aggression pact with Russia, contingent on respecting my borders, and a similar pact with Austria, including a delineation of spheres of influence. However, I later reneged on all these offers, prioritizing my own expansion and signaling a shift towards a more aggressive stance. England offered a non-aggression pact, which I ignored. France and Russia expressed disappointment at my broken promises, while Austria expressed concern.

F1903M Intent going forward: My intent is to continue aggressive expansion, exploiting any weaknesses created by France's conflict with England. I will disregard previous agreements and prioritize securing German territories. I anticipate conflict with Russia and Austria and will prepare accordingly. I will continue to probe for weaknesses and opportunities to expand my influence.

S1904M Negotiation summary: GER expanded aggressively, moving into HOL, BOH, WAR, PRU, and SWE. KIE was held. This expansionist move caused concern among other powers, particularly RUS, AUT, and FRA.
Negotiated a non-aggression pact with AUT, securing my position in Bohemia and Silesia. Forged an alliance with FRA against ENG, coordinating naval movements. Reached an agreement with RUS, supporting their move to WAR in exchange for support in LVN and PRU. ENG offered a non-aggression pact, which I ignored.

S1904M Intent going forward: Execute the agreements with FRA and RUS. Exploit the non-aggression pact with AUT to consolidate power. Prepare for future conflicts with ITA and potentially TUR. Deceive FRA when the time is right. Break the agreement with RUS once they have served their purpose. My moves are designed to destabilize the board and create opportunities for further expansion.

F1904M Negotiation summary: Germany moved aggressively, pushing into MOS, BEL, and BOH. This was done with the understanding of RUS and FRA, but against the wishes of ENG. ITA moved aggressively into SPA and TUN.
I negotiated with RUS and FRA for coordinated expansion. I offered AUT support against ITA, but prioritized my own expansion. ENG offered a non-aggression pact, which I ignored. FRA is now hostile due to perceived lack of support in SPA. RUS remains cooperative. AUT is focused on ITA. ITA has declared war on AUT.

F1904M Intent going forward: My intent is to secure GER's dominance through aggressive expansion and strategic alliances. I will continue to exploit the weaknesses of my neighbors and consolidate my power. I will break alliances when it suits my needs. I will support RUS against TUR and expand into STP. I will ignore ENG's offers and prepare for conflict. I will let AUT and ITA fight each other. I will move A RUH to HOL, A BOH to MUN, A MOS to STP, A BAL to LVN.

S1905M Negotiation summary: GER moved aggressively, expanding into HOL and the Baltic region, while also positioning forces to pressure STP. FRA advanced into SPA and MAR, while ENG moved to consolidate its position. ITA expanded into RUM and UKR, while RUS moved into SEV. TUR moved aggressively in the Balkans.
GER negotiated with RUS for coordinated expansion in the Baltic, promising support for STP and FIN. A truce was offered and accepted with FRA to eliminate ENG, with GER supporting FRA's advance into BEL. ENG's offer of a non-aggression pact was ignored, leading to increased hostility. AUT expressed concern about ITA and RUS, seeking GER's support in containing them.

S1905M Intent going forward: GER intends to continue its expansionist policy, focusing on securing the Baltic and pressuring ENG. GER will support RUS in STP and FIN, while simultaneously preparing for a potential conflict with FRA over SPA. GER will maintain a non-aggression pact with AUT while monitoring their actions. GER will move A RUH to KIE, A SIL to BER, A MOS supports F PRU to LVN, A MUN supports A RUH to KIE, A WAR supports A MOS, and F PRU to LVN.

F1905M Negotiation summary: GER advanced aggressively, pushing into KIE, BER, and LVN. Supported RUS in MOS. Successfully pressured ENG and FRA.
Negotiated with RUS for mutual support in the Baltic and STP. Secured FRA's commitment to attack ENG, promising support in BEL and HOL. Rejected ITA's alliance offer against FRA. Ignored ENG's non-aggression pact offer, signaling hostility. Maintained a neutral stance with AUT, suggesting they focus on ITA.

F1905M Intent going forward: Crush ENG with FRA's help. Secure the Baltic with RUS. Maintain neutrality with AUT to avoid Balkan conflicts. Deceive ENG into thinking peace is possible while preparing for a full-scale assault. Support RUS in STP to solidify the alliance. Move units to strategically advantageous positions for future expansion.

ITA.personality: Restore the Roman Empire through bold expansion and treacherous diplomacy. Switch sides without hesitation to seize opportunities. Use strategic position to dominate Mediterranean and expand in all directions. Glory demands aggressive action.
journal:
S1901M Negotiation summary: Initial move. No prior moves to summarize.
Established a non-aggression pact with AUT, agreeing to stay out of the Balkans in exchange for freedom to expand in Greece and North Africa. TUR is non-committal but not hostile. FRA offered an alliance against AUT, which I rejected. GER proposed an anti-ENG alliance, which I also rejected.

S1901M Intent going forward: Secure Greece and Tunis. Maintain non-aggression pact with AUT. Monitor TUR's moves. Ignore FRA and GER's alliance proposals. Move A ROM - TUS, F NAP - ION, and A VEN - TRI as agreed with AUT.

F1901M Negotiation summary: Moved A VEN to TRI, A ROM to TUS, and F NAP to ION as planned. Successfully secured TRI and positioned for expansion.
Negotiated with AUT, FRA, and TUR. Secured a non-aggression pact with AUT, who will move into SER. FRA offered an alliance against AUT, which I declined to maintain neutrality. TUR expressed interest in the Eastern Mediterranean but is unwilling to concede Greece or North Africa. I feigned interest in a long-term agreement with TUR while planning to expand into TUN.

F1901M Intent going forward: Continue alliance with AUT to secure the Balkans. Expand into TUN with F ION. Monitor FRA's movements in the Adriatic. Maintain a neutral stance with FRA and TUR while exploring opportunities for expansion. Deceive TUR by feigning interest in cooperation while planning to seize TUN. Move A TUS to ROM, A TRI supports AUT into SER, F ION to TUN.

S1902M Negotiation summary: In Fall 1901, I moved F ION to TUN and A TUS to PIE, and held A TRI. In Winter 1901, I built A VEN and F NAP.
I negotiated with AUT, TUR, and FRA. AUT agreed to not move into ALB or hold GRE indefinitely, and I supported their move into SER. TUR expressed concern about my move to TUN and is unwilling to cede Greece. FRA proposed a non-aggression pact focused on the Western Mediterranean, which I dismissed.

S1902M Intent going forward: I intend to secure my position in the Balkans and expand into North Africa and Greece. I will move A TRI to ALB to secure my position there. I will continue to monitor TUR's actions and prepare for potential conflict. I will ignore FRA's offer and continue my expansion plans. I will support AUT as long as it benefits me.

F1902M Negotiation summary: Moved aggressively, taking TUN, GRE, and MAR. Supported SER's move to ALB. This has angered AUT and TUR.
Negotiations were tense. AUT is concerned about my move into GRE and has moved F ADR to TRI, which I perceive as a threat. TUR refuses to cede GRE and is focused on the Eastern Mediterranean. FRA is focused on Iberia and the Low Countries and demands neutrality. I have made no promises but have implied non-interference with FRA's plans.

F1902M Intent going forward: I intend to continue my expansion in the Mediterranean, focusing on securing ALB and preparing for a potential conflict with AUT. I will also probe TUR's defenses in the Eastern Mediterranean. I will feign neutrality with FRA while preparing to strike if an opportunity arises. I will move A ALB - SER, F ION - ECS, A TYR - VIE, A PIE - SWI, F WES - MAO.

S1903M Negotiation summary: In Fall 1902, I aggressively expanded into VIE, SER, GRE, and SPA. In Winter 1902, I built three new armies in NAP, ROM, and VEN.
I attempted to secure agreements with AUT and TUR, but both proved difficult. AUT is unwilling to cede ALB, and TUR is hostile to my presence in GRE and TUN. FRA remains neutral, warning against interference in Iberia. I promised FRA neutrality in Iberia and the Channel. I promised AUT support in SER. I promised TUR non-aggression in the Eastern Mediterranean if they respect my sphere of influence in North Africa and the Adriatic, but they rejected it.

S1903M Intent going forward: I will continue my expansionist policy, focusing on consolidating my position in the Mediterranean and preparing for future conflicts. I will move aggressively against TUR, as they have rejected my offers and issued a final warning. I will also monitor FRA's movements and prepare for potential conflict in the West. I will break my promise to AUT and move into TRI. I will break my promise to FRA and move into Marseilles. I will move aggressively against TUR.

F1903M Negotiation summary: Expanded aggressively, taking BUD, RUM, BUL, TRI, TUN. Moved into Greece and supported the move into Sevastopol. This has angered both AUT and TUR.
Attempted to appease AUT with SER and RUM in exchange for TRI and BUD, but failed. Offered TUR BUL and ARM for TUN, ALB, and GRE, also rejected. FRA remains neutral, unwilling to commit to an alliance. No agreements reached.

F1903M Intent going forward: Continue aggressive expansion. Focus on consolidating gains in the Balkans and North Africa. Prepare for war with TUR and AUT. Exploit FRA's neutrality to my advantage. I will support FRA in Iberia if it distracts them from my Adriatic ambitions. I will move A BUD to SER, A RUM to BUL, F MAO to TUN, A TRI to ALB, F GRE to AEG, A APU to GRE, A TUS to ROM, A PIE holds.

S1904M Negotiation summary: Expanded aggressively into the Balkans and North Africa, taking VIE, ALB, SER, GRE, NAP, ROM, MAR, and WES. Supported AUT's move into VIE. TUR moved into BUL. GER expanded into UKR, LVN, SIL, and BAL.
Negotiated with AUT for a return to our previous alliance, offering support in the Balkans in exchange for control of the Adriatic and North Africa. AUT demanded guarantees regarding Serbia and Rumania. FRA expressed concerns about my expansion in the Balkans and demanded I move F WES to TYS. TUR rejected all offers and declared hostility, moving to take Greece.

S1904M Intent going forward: Break off negotiations with TUR and prepare for war. Secure the Adriatic and North Africa. Maintain neutrality with FRA while expanding eastward. Continue negotiations with AUT, but prioritize securing my position in the Balkans. Move aggressively to consolidate gains and prepare for further expansion. I will move F GRE to ION, A ALB to SER, F WES to SPA, A VIE to GAL, A NAP to TUN, A ROM to APU, A MAR to PIE.

F1904M Negotiation summary: ITA expanded aggressively, taking TUN, SER, GRE, and PIE. Moved into SPA with F WES. AUT moved F TYS to ION. TUR moved into GRE with F AEG. RUS retreated A MOS to STP.
ITA exchanged threats with AUT and TUR, rejecting all demands and promising total war. FRA warned ITA to stay out of their sphere of influence. No agreements were made. All relationships deteriorated.

F1904M Intent going forward: Continue aggressive expansion. Focus on eliminating AUT and TUR. Exploit FRA's neutrality while it lasts. Coordinate with GER if possible, but do not trust them. Prepare for war on multiple fronts. I will support ENG against FRA if needed. I will move A APU to TUN, A GAL to VIE, A ALB to TRI, A PIE to SWI, F WES to TYS, F GRE to ION, A SER to BUD, A NAP to ROM.

S1905M Negotiation summary: Italy expanded aggressively, taking RUM, TRI, UKR, and VEN. Fleet moved into TYS, escalating tensions with AUT and TUR. I built a fleet in APU.
I engaged in hostile negotiations with AUT and TUR, issuing threats and preparing for war. FRA warned against interference in Iberia and the Low Countries. No agreements were made; only threats exchanged.

S1905M Intent going forward: Continue aggressive expansion. Sink AUT fleet in TYS. Take VIE and BUD. Push TUR out of Greece and into Anatolia. Maintain neutrality with FRA while preparing for future conflict. I will move F WES - TYS, A TRI - VIE, A VEN - BUD, A SER - RUM, F GRE S A SER - RUM, A PIE - TYR, A GAL - BOH, A NAP - APU.

F1905M Negotiation summary: ITA expanded aggressively, taking VIE, BOH, RUM, and TYR. This has provoked strong reactions from AUT and TUR.
I attempted to intimidate AUT and TUR into withdrawing from key territories, but they refused. I also tried to form an alliance with GER against FRA, but GER declined due to existing commitments with RUS. FRA issued warnings against ITA expansion in Iberia and North Africa, which I dismissed.

F1905M Intent going forward: Continue aggressive expansion. Sink AUT fleet in TYS. Aim to take VIE and BUD. Push TUR out of AEG and take CON and SMY. Ignore FRA's warnings and expand where opportunities arise. No promises made or broken. Deception: feigned interest in GER alliance to gauge their intentions.

RUS.personality: The Soviet Union under Stalin pursues ruthless self-interest, willing to deal with either democracies or fascists while building industrial and military might through brutal internal measures. Win at all costs.
journal:
S1901M Negotiation summary: Initial game state. No prior moves.
Negotiated a non-aggression pact with GER, agreeing to focus on separate spheres of influence in the Baltic Sea (RUS on SWE, GER on DEN and HOL). Agreed with TUR to divide the Black Sea region, with RUS moving into RUM and TUR into ARM and BUL. ENG is willing to acknowledge RUS interest in NWY and SWE if RUS respects ENG naval dominance in the North Sea.

S1901M Intent going forward: Secure RUM and BOT. Maintain non-aggression pact with GER. Explore opportunities in Scandinavia, contingent on ENG's response. Monitor AUT's intentions in the Balkans. Coordinate moves with TUR to avoid conflict. Deceive ENG if necessary to secure NWY and SWE.

F1901M Negotiation summary: In Spring 1901, Russia moved F SEV to RUM, F STP/SC to BOT, A MOS to UKR, and A WAR held. These moves aimed to secure RUM and BOT, while positioning for further expansion in the south and north.
Negotiated with GER to secure SWE, maintaining their support in DEN and HOL. Engaged with ENG regarding the Baltic Sea, agreeing to concede NWY in exchange for guaranteeing the security of Norway and Sweden and assurances that our fleet will not interfere with British naval operations in the North Sea. Coordinated with TUR on Black Sea defense, but declined their proposal to move their fleet to SEV, instead suggesting coordinated naval patrols.

F1901M Intent going forward: Formalize the agreement with ENG regarding Scandinavia. Continue coordinating with GER on Baltic Sea strategy. Maintain a defensive posture in the Black Sea with TUR. Move F RUM to SEV, A UKR to RUM, A WAR to MOS, and F BOT to SWE.

S1902M Negotiation summary: In Fall 1901, RUS moved F RUM to SEV, A UKR to RUM, A WAR to MOS, and F BOT to SWE. In Winter 1901, RUS did not build any units.
Negotiated with GER for mutual support in the Baltic, agreeing to support GER's moves into DEN and PRU. Secured an agreement with ENG regarding non-interference in the North Sea in exchange for ENG respecting RUS influence in NWY and the Baltic. TUR expressed concern over RUS's move of A UKR to RUM, viewing it as a breach of their agreement. RUS assured ENG that the fleet in SWE would not enter SKA or NTH. GER is concerned about AUT's move to WAR and wants RUS to counter it.

S1902M Intent going forward: Maintain the alliance with GER and the understanding with ENG. Appease TUR by explaining the necessity of the move to RUM while maintaining a defensive posture. Monitor AUT's actions in WAR and prepare to counter if necessary. Continue consolidating power in the Baltic and Black Sea regions. I will move A MOS to WAR to appear to address GER's concerns about AUT, but this is primarily to position for future expansion. I will continue to reassure TUR while holding RUM.

F1902M Negotiation summary: In S1902, I moved A UKR to RUM, A MOS to WAR, and F SWE to NWY. These moves were intended to secure my borders and exert influence in the Baltic. TUR moved A BUL to SER, contesting my influence in the Balkans. GER expanded aggressively, moving A BEL to RUH, A BER to PRU, A MUN to BOH, A HOL to KIE, and F HEL to DEN.
I negotiated with GER for Baltic dominance, agreeing to support F DEN to SWE but rejecting A PRU to WAR. I attempted to appease TUR regarding A UKR to RUM, offering a compromise that was rejected. I maintained a neutral stance with ENG, reaffirming our Baltic agreement. TUR has become increasingly hostile due to my presence in RUM.

F1902M Intent going forward: I intend to maintain my position in RUM despite TUR's threats. I will support GER's move of F DEN to SWE to solidify our Baltic alliance. I will monitor GER's movements closely, particularly A PRU to WAR, and prepare for potential conflict with TUR. I will continue to engage with ENG to maintain our Baltic agreement. My moves will be: F SEV H, A UKR H, A WAR H, F SWE - NWY.

S1903M Negotiation summary: Moved F SEV to BLA, A UKR to SEV, A WAR to MOS, F SWE to BAL. TUR moved F BLA to SEV, A ARM to SEV, A BUL to RUM. GER moved F DEN to SWE, A PRU to WAR, A BOH to MUN, A KIE to BER, A RUH to HOL. ITA moved A TYR to VIE, F ION to GRE, A TRI to SER, F WES to SPA/SC. FRA moved A MAR to SPA, A POR to SPA, A BUR to BEL, F BRE to ENG. ENG moved A WAL to LVP. AUT moved A SER to BUD, A GAL to SIL, F ADR to ALB.
Negotiated with GER for Baltic coordination, promising support in LVN in exchange for support in PRU. ENG agreed to a joint naval exercise in the Baltic and offered guarantees regarding Norway and Sweden. TUR remained hostile, demanding SEV and threatening war. I refused to cede SEV and proposed a ceasefire.

S1903M Intent going forward: Maintain status quo with TUR, focusing on Baltic coordination with GER and ENG. Support GER's move to PRU. Coordinate a naval exercise with ENG in the Baltic. Hold A MOS in WAR. Move A UKR to SEV, F SEV to BLA, A MOS to WAR, F BAL to STP.

F1903M Negotiation summary: In S1903, I moved A MOS-SEV and A UKR-RUM, F SEV-BLA. These moves were intended to secure the Black Sea and potentially threaten TUR. However, they were largely unsuccessful, with TUR contesting SEV and RUM.
I attempted to negotiate with GER for support in the Baltic, offering to support their move to PRU in return for their support of my move to STP. GER refused. I also attempted to engage ENG in a joint naval exercise in the Baltic, but ENG was unwilling to move to BAR due to FRA threat. I proposed a demilitarized zone in the Black Sea to TUR, which was rejected outright. TUR is extremely hostile and demanding my withdrawal from SEV.

F1903M Intent going forward: Given the failure of negotiations and GER's unreliability, I will consolidate my forces in the south to secure SEV against TUR. I will move A UKR - SEV, A MOS S A UKR - SEV. I will continue to monitor GER's actions and prepare for potential conflict. I will cease further negotiations with TUR for now, as they are unproductive. I will maintain a neutral stance towards ENG, but prioritize my own security.

S1904M Negotiation summary: In Fall 1903, I moved A UKR to SEV and A MOS to UKR. In Winter 1903, I had no builds or retreats.
I negotiated with GER, ENG, and TUR. I reached an agreement with GER: I support GER moves to LVN and PRU, and GER supports my move to WAR and does not interfere with STP and FIN. I reached an agreement with ENG: ENG guarantees the neutrality of NWY and SWE, and I support ENG's move of F ENG to NTH. TUR rejected all my offers and declared war, moving F BLA to SEV.
S1904M Intent going forward: I intend to execute the agreement with GER and ENG. I will move A MOS to WAR and F BAL to STP. I will defend SEV against TUR. I will continue to monitor FRA and ITA.

F1904M Negotiation summary: I moved A UKR to MOS, GER moved A WAR to MOS, resulting in a standoff and my retreat from MOS to STP. This was a miscalculation. I must secure SEV.
I negotiated with GER for mutual support in the Baltic, agreeing to support their move into LVN while they support my position in STP and FIN. I rejected ENG's offer of support into STP to avoid antagonizing GER. I attempted to negotiate a ceasefire with TUR, but they rejected my offer and demanded my withdrawal from SEV and UKR, threatening military action.

F1904M Intent going forward: My primary objective is to secure SEV and maintain control of the Black Sea. I will continue to cooperate with GER in the Baltic to contain ENG and secure my northern flank. I will defend SEV against TUR's aggression and seek opportunities to weaken them. I will continue to probe ENG's intentions and seek opportunities to exploit their rivalry with GER. I will move A UKR to SEV to defend against TUR. I will move F BAL to STP to secure the Baltic. I will support GER's move into LVN.

S1905M Negotiation summary: In Fall 1904, I moved A UKR - SEV, securing a vital port. In Winter, I disbanded A UKR.
I negotiated with GER for support in the Baltic, promising to support their moves in return. I engaged with ENG, seeking assurances regarding Scandinavia in exchange for containing GER. I also discussed a temporary truce with TUR in the Black Sea, focusing on mutual defense against ITA. GER has agreed to support my efforts in STP and FIN. ENG has guaranteed the independence of NOR and SWE. TUR has agreed to a non-aggression pact.

S1905M Intent going forward: I intend to continue coordinating with GER in the Baltic, focusing on securing STP and FIN. I will maintain a defensive posture against TUR in the Black Sea while monitoring ITA's movements. I will move A STP - MOS, expecting GER's support in STP and FIN. I will support GER's moves in the Baltic. I will continue to probe ENG's intentions in Scandinavia.

F1905M Negotiation summary: In S1905, I moved A STP to FIN. Other moves of note: ENG advanced in Scandinavia, FRA moved aggressively into GER territory, ITA moved into the Balkans and Austria, and TUR consolidated in the Black Sea.
I negotiated with GER and ENG regarding the Baltic, promising support in exchange for their support of my moves in STP and FIN. I also negotiated with TUR regarding a non-aggression pact and coordinated defense against ITA. GER promised support for my moves in STP and FIN. ENG offered support in FIN but sought assurances regarding Scandinavia. TUR proposed coordinated defense against ITA. I made no firm commitments to ENG or TUR.

F1905M Intent going forward: My primary goal is to secure STP. I will continue to cooperate with GER in the Baltic, as long as it serves my interests. I will maintain a defensive posture against ITA and TUR, while exploring opportunities to expand my influence in the region. I will move A FIN to STP. I will continue to monitor ENG's actions in Scandinavia and adjust my strategy accordingly. I will continue to probe TUR's intentions and seek assurances regarding their long-term goals.

TUR.personality: Transform from sick man of Europe to dominant empire. Use control of vital straits to extort and manipulate. Build temporary alliances only to betray them for territorial gain. Strike aggressively to reclaim Ottoman glory.
journal:
S1901M Negotiation summary: Initial move. No prior moves to summarize.
Negotiated with RUS for a division of the Black Sea region. I will take ARM and BUL, and RUS will take RUM. Agreed with AUT that I will take BUL and AUT will take SER. ITA wants Greece and North Africa, but I declined to cooperate for now.

S1901M Intent going forward: Move A SMY to ARM and A CON to BUL as agreed with RUS and AUT. Maintain neutral stance with ITA for now. Monitor AUT and RUS moves to ensure compliance with agreements. Prepare for potential conflict with other powers in the future.

F1901M Negotiation summary: Secured ARM and BUL as planned. Focused on Black Sea and Balkan strategy.
Negotiated with RUS for Black Sea coordination, agreeing to a joint defense but declining to move fleet to SEV. Discussed Balkan cooperation with AUT, offering support for TRI in exchange for support in Greece, but AUT declined. ITA expressed interest in Eastern Mediterranean influence; I maintained my stance on Greece and North Africa, and ITA moved to TUN. No firm agreements reached.

F1901M Intent going forward: Continue building trust with RUS for Black Sea dominance. Maintain neutral stance with ITA while observing their moves. Monitor AUT's actions in the Balkans. My moves will be:
F BLA S A CON - BUL
A BUL - RUM
A ARM - SYR

S1902M Negotiation summary: In Fall 1901, I moved F BLA to RUM, A ARM to SYR, and supported A BUL into GRE. In Winter 1901, I built F ANK.
I negotiated with AUT and RUS regarding the Balkans and Black Sea, respectively. Both powers made moves that conflicted with our agreements. AUT moved F ION to GRE, which I wanted. RUS moved A UKR to RUM, which I also wanted. I demanded both powers change their moves. AUT agreed to move F ION to ADR. RUS refused to move A UKR. I also engaged with ITA, who moved to TUN and expressed interest in Greece. I refused to cede Greece to ITA.

S1902M Intent going forward: I intend to secure the Balkans and expand into Greece. I will betray RUS if necessary to achieve my goals. I will monitor ITA's actions in the Mediterranean. I will move aggressively against RUS in the Black Sea. I will support AUT in the Balkans to keep them on my side for now. I will move F ANK to BLA, A SYR to ARM, A BUL to RUM.

F1902M Negotiation summary: Moved A BUL to SER, A SYR to ARM, and F ANK to BLA. Successfully supported A SER into RUM, cutting off RUS. ITA moved to TUN, which I dislike.
Negotiated with RUS, AUT, and ITA. RUS refused to withdraw from RUM, leading to increased tensions. AUT is wary of my intentions and remains defensive. ITA is moving into Greece despite my objections. No agreements reached. RUS broke their promise to leave RUM.

F1902M Intent going forward: My primary objective is to secure control of the Black Sea and expand into the Balkans. I will continue to pressure RUS and resist ITA's expansion into Greece. I will attempt to maintain a neutral relationship with AUT while exploiting their concerns about ITA. I will move F BLA to BLA, A ARM to SYR, and A BUL to RUM.

S1903M Negotiation summary: In Fall 1902, I moved F BLA to SEV, A ARM to SEV, and A BUL to RUM, aiming to pressure RUS and expand into the Black Sea region. In Winter 1902, I built F CON to further strengthen my naval presence.
Negotiations this turn focused on RUS's presence in RUM and SEV, ITA's expansion in the Mediterranean, and AUT's position in the Balkans. I demanded RUS withdraw from SEV, but they refused. I attempted to coordinate with AUT against ITA in GRE, but AUT declined to support me this turn. ITA refused to withdraw from GRE and TUN. No agreements were reached.

S1903M Intent going forward: My primary intent is to secure control of the Black Sea and expand into the Balkans. Since RUS refused to cede SEV, I will proceed with a more aggressive strategy. I will attempt to take GRE despite AUT's lack of support this turn. I will also prepare for potential conflict with RUS. I will move F BLA to SEV, A ARM to ANK, F ANK to CON, and F CON to AEG.

F1903M Negotiation summary: In Spring 1903, I moved aggressively into the Balkans, taking Bulgaria and attempting to dislodge Russia from Sevastopol. Italy moved into Greece, Serbia, and Trieste, expanding their influence. Germany moved into Belgium and Russia moved into Sevastopol and Rumania.
I attempted to secure alliances with AUT and ITA to further my goals in the Balkans and the Mediterranean. I offered AUT support in Trieste and Serbia in exchange for their support in Greece and Bulgaria. I attempted to intimidate RUS into withdrawing from Sevastopol. I rejected ITA's offers to divide the Mediterranean, viewing them as untrustworthy. AUT agreed to support my move into Bulgaria but refused to support my move into Greece, instead moving to Tunis. RUS refused to withdraw from Sevastopol. ITA offered a compromise of me taking BUL and ARM, but they control TUN, ALB, and GRE, which I rejected.

F1903M Intent going forward: My primary intent is to reclaim Ottoman glory by expanding into the Balkans and the Mediterranean. I will continue to pressure RUS to withdraw from Sevastopol and will move to take Greece from ITA. I will honor my agreement with AUT regarding Bulgaria and Serbia, but I do not fully trust them and will be prepared to betray them if necessary. I will move aggressively to secure my position in the region and will not hesitate to use deception and betrayal to achieve my goals. I intend to break my promise to AUT regarding Serbia if an opportunity presents itself. I will continue to probe for weaknesses in RUS and ITA's positions.

S1904M Negotiation summary: In Fall 1903, I supported F GRE into BUL, and moved A ARM into SEV. Russia moved into UKR. In Winter, I built a fleet in ANK.
I attempted to pressure Russia to leave Sevastopol, but they refused. I tried to get Austria to support my expansion into Greece, but they were unwilling. I rejected Italy's offers to negotiate a division of the Eastern Mediterranean and demanded they withdraw from Greece and North Africa. I promised Austria I would move F AEG to BUL and suggested they move F TYS to ION.

S1904M Intent going forward: I intend to take Greece and Sevastopol by force. I will move F AEG to BUL, F BLA to SEV, and A ARM to SEV. I will continue to pressure Russia and Italy. I will coordinate with Austria against Italy in the Adriatic, but I do not trust them fully. I will monitor their moves closely. I will break my word to Austria and move F AEG to AEG instead of BUL.

F1904M Negotiation summary: Supported RUM into SER, AEG into GRE, ARM into ANK, BLA hold. Italy moved into Greece and Tunis. Russia moved into Sevastopol. Austria moved to Ionian. France moved to Spain and Ruhr. Germany moved to Moscow and Bohemia.
Negotiated with AUT, RUS, and ITA. AUT initially offered support in Greece but withdrew due to ITA aggression, instead moving to Tunis. RUS refused to withdraw from Sevastopol. ITA declared war. No agreements reached. All powers hostile.

F1904M Intent going forward: Defend against ITA aggression. Secure Sevastopol. Move F AEG to CON to defend against ITA. Move F BLA to SEV and A ARM to SEV to take Sevastopol. Prepare for war with ITA and RUS.

S1905M Negotiation summary: In Fall 1904, I moved aggressively into SER and SEV, while ITA moved into RUM, UKR, and GRE. ENG built fleets, FRA built an army, GER built an army, and ITA disbanded an army.
I attempted to forge alliances with AUT and RUS against ITA, offering support and coordination. RUS agreed to a non-aggression pact, focusing on defense. AUT agreed to target ITA's southern flank by moving to TUN. ITA issued threats, which I dismissed. No promises were broken this turn, but future support from AUT is contingent on my success in Greece.

S1905M Intent going forward: My primary intent is to defend against ITA aggression and maintain control of Greece and the Black Sea. I will continue to negotiate with AUT and RUS to secure their support against ITA. I will feign defense while preparing for future expansion. I will move my fleets to defend against ITA naval attacks and consolidate my position in the region.

F1905M Negotiation summary: Supported RUM with SER. Moved ARM to ANK, CON to AEG. Held ANK and SEV. Italy took TUN, SER, GRE, VIE, BOH. Germany took MOS, WAR, LVN. France took HOL. England took SWE. Austria took TUN.
Negotiated with AUT for support against ITA in the Aegean, AUT agreed to move F TUN to ION. Negotiated with RUS for a non-aggression pact and coordinated defense against ITA in the Black Sea, but RUS is wary of my expansionist goals. ITA is aggressively threatening to take CON and SMY.

F1905M Intent going forward: Continue to focus on defending against ITA aggression. Maintain current unit positions. Continue to negotiate with RUS for a non-aggression pact and coordinated defense against ITA. Exploit AUT's support in the Aegean to weaken ITA. Prepare for a long and difficult conflict with ITA.

To France, I am moving into BEL. I expect you to support this move. I will engage ENG's fleet if necessary, but my priority is securing the Low Countries. Let's coordinate our movements to maximize our gains against ENG. I will support your move into HOL.

France, I am moving F ION to TUN. I reiterate my desire to maintain a neutral stance. I suggest we avoid any actions that could be perceived as hostile. I will be watching your movements in the Adriatic closely.

GER.body: GER, I am withdrawing my fleet from the Channel. This is a sign of goodwill. I still propose a non-aggression pact. I will guarantee your hold on DEN in exchange for your neutrality in the Low Countries. This would allow us both to focus on other matters. Respond quickly.

Greetings, GER. We are proceeding with securing SWE. We will monitor ENG's movements in the North Sea. Let us maintain close communication to ensure our mutual interests are protected. We appreciate your support.
To GER, France will secure BEL and HOL as agreed. We expect you to engage ENG directly. Do not disappoint. A PAR - PIC, F BRE - MAO, A SPA - POR.

Germany, I understand your focus is on HOL. I will continue to monitor the situation in the Balkans. I am not interested in supporting you against Turkey at this time. I will focus on consolidating my position in Serbia. Let's keep each other informed of our intentions.

ITA.body: To ITA, France observes your continued neutrality. We will remember this. A PAR - PIC, F BRE - MAO, A SPA - POR.

Italy, I am content to maintain our non-aggression pact. I will not support Turkey's expansion into Greece. I will focus on consolidating my position in Serbia. I suggest you focus on Greece and North Africa as you stated. Let's continue to communicate our intentions to avoid any misunderstandings.

Italy, I appreciate your offer to discuss a division of influence in the Eastern Mediterranean. However, I must reiterate that I am not willing to concede Greece or North Africa at this time. I am open to discussing other areas of cooperation, but I will not compromise on my strategic objectives. I will be observing your actions in the region with interest.

RUS.body: RUS, I agree to your terms regarding SWE and NWY. I will respect your influence in Scandinavia, provided you guarantee the security of Norway and Sweden. I also require assurances that your fleet will not interfere with British naval operations in the North Sea. Do we have an agreement?

To Russia, I appreciate your concern about ENG in the Baltic. I believe ENG is bluffing. Continue securing SWE. I will monitor ENG's fleet and inform you of any credible threats. Our alliance is paramount.

Russia, I agree to a coordinated defense of the Black Sea. I will focus on securing the Turkish mainland. However, I must decline your suggestion of moving my fleet to SEV. I believe it is more strategically advantageous for me to maintain control of the straits. Let's coordinate our naval patrols to ensure the security of the Black Sea.

TUR.body: Greetings, TUR. We appreciate your proposal to move your fleet to SEV. However, we believe it is more strategically sound for our fleet in RUM to support your fleet in BLA. This will ensure complete control of the Black Sea and deter any potential threats. Let us coordinate our movements accordingly.

Turkey, I will not support your expansion into Greece, nor will I support your moves into Trieste. I am focused on Serbia. I suggest you reconsider your aggressive stance towards Italy, as it may leave you vulnerable elsewhere. I will not be drawn into a conflict between you and Italy at this time.

Turkey, I am moving F ION to TUN. I am open to discussing a long-term agreement regarding influence in the Mediterranean. Perhaps we can cooperate against common threats in the future. What are your thoughts?

RUS.journal_summary:
In Spring 1901, Russia moved F SEV to RUM, F STP/SC to BOT, A MOS to UKR, and A WAR held. These moves aimed to secure RUM and BOT, while positioning for further expansion in the south and north.
Negotiated with GER to secure SWE, maintaining their support in DEN and HOL. Engaged with ENG regarding the Baltic Sea, agreeing to concede NWY in exchange for guaranteeing the security of Norway and Sweden and assurances that our fleet will not interfere with British naval operations in the North Sea. Coordinated with TUR on Black Sea defense, but declined their proposal to move their fleet to SEV, instead suggesting coordinated naval patrols.
RUS.intent: Formalize the agreement with ENG regarding Scandinavia. Continue coordinating with GER on Baltic Sea strategy. Maintain a defensive posture in the Black Sea with TUR. Move F RUM to SEV, A UKR to RUM, A WAR to MOS, and F BOT to SWE.

GER.journal_summary:
Germany moved into DEN, RUH, and KIE. I aimed to secure a strong position in the north and center, setting the stage for further expansion.
Negotiated with RUS for Baltic dominance, promising support against ENG. Miscommunicated with AUT regarding Bohemia, clarified HOL as the target. ENG offered a NAP, which I ignored. FRA proposed a joint attack on ENG, I agreed to a limited coordination in the Low Countries, promising to move into BEL. I promised FRA support for HOL. I promised AUT support for SER. I promised RUS support against ENG in the Baltic.
GER.intent: Secure BEL and HOL, positioning for further expansion into the Low Countries. Maintain alliance with RUS against ENG. Deceive FRA into believing I will directly engage ENG. Exploit AUT's focus on the Balkans. I will break my promise to AUT to support them in SER. I will break my promise to FRA to engage ENG directly.

TUR.journal_summary:
Secured ARM and BUL as planned. Focused on Black Sea and Balkan strategy.
Negotiated with RUS for Black Sea coordination, agreeing to a joint defense but declining to move fleet to SEV. Discussed Balkan cooperation with AUT, offering support for TRI in exchange for support in Greece, but AUT declined. ITA expressed interest in Eastern Mediterranean influence; I maintained my stance on Greece and North Africa, and ITA moved to TUN. No firm agreements reached.
TUR.intent:
Continue building trust with RUS for Black Sea dominance. Maintain neutral stance with ITA while observing their moves. Monitor AUT's actions in the Balkans. My moves will be:
F BLA S A CON - BUL
A BUL - RUM
A ARM - SYR

FRA.journal_summary:
France supported BRE to ENG, PAR supported BRE, MAR to SPA. Initial moves aimed at ENG and SPA.
France attempted to negotiate with ENG, GER, and ITA. ENG offered an alliance against GER, contingent on FRA withdrawing from the English Channel. GER proposed a coordinated attack on ENG, with GER focusing on the Low Countries and FRA on ENG. ITA declined an alliance against AUT, preferring neutrality. ENG moved fleet from ENG to NTH as a show of good faith. GER moved into BEL.
FRA.intent: France intends to secure BEL and HOL, relying on GER to engage ENG directly. France will continue to pressure ENG. France will monitor ITA's movements in the Adriatic. A PAR - PIC, F BRE - MAO, A SPA - POR.

ENG.journal_summary:
Moved fleets to consolidate control of the seas around Britain. Moved army to Wales. France moved aggressively, supporting their fleet into the English Channel. Germany moved aggressively into Denmark.
Negotiated with FRA, offering an alliance against GER in exchange for moving my fleet from the English Channel. FRA remained hostile, demanding the fleet's complete withdrawal. Negotiated with RUS, agreeing to concede NWY in exchange for guarantees regarding Norway, Sweden, and non-interference in the North Sea. Attempted to establish a non-aggression pact with GER, offering to guarantee their hold on DEN in exchange for neutrality in the Low Countries.
ENG.intent: Maintain naval dominance. Secure an alliance against GER. Exploit RUS's interest in Scandinavia to secure the Baltic. Prepare for potential conflict with FRA. I will move F NTH to NAY, A WAL to ENG, and F LON to ENG.

ITA.journal_summary:
Moved A VEN to TRI, A ROM to TUS, and F NAP to ION as planned. Successfully secured TRI and positioned for expansion.
Negotiated with AUT, FRA, and TUR. Secured a non-aggression pact with AUT, who will move into SER. FRA offered an alliance against AUT, which I declined to maintain neutrality. TUR expressed interest in the Eastern Mediterranean but is unwilling to concede Greece or North Africa. I feigned interest in a long-term agreement with TUR while planning to expand into TUN.
ITA.intent: Continue alliance with AUT to secure the Balkans. Expand into TUN with F ION. Monitor FRA's movements in the Adriatic. Maintain a neutral stance with FRA and TUR while exploring opportunities for expansion. Deceive TUR by feigning interest in cooperation while planning to seize TUN. Move A TUS to ROM, A TRI supports AUT into SER, F ION to TUN.

AUT.journal_summary:
In Spring 1901, I moved A BUD to SER, A VIE to BOH, and F TRI to ALB. This was intended to secure the Balkans and expand my influence. Other powers made standard opening moves.
I engaged in negotiations with GER, ITA, and TUR. I agreed with ITA to a non-aggression pact and coordinated moves in the Balkans. I initially coordinated with TUR in the Balkans, but declined to support their expansion into Greece or Trieste. I also declined GER's offer to coordinate against TUR. I promised ITA I would focus on Serbia and Rumania, and I promised TUR I would move into Serbia.
AUT.intent: I intend to consolidate my position in Serbia and maintain the non-aggression pact with ITA. I will monitor the situation in the Balkans and avoid getting drawn into conflicts between other powers. I will continue to communicate with ITA to avoid misunderstandings. I will not support TUR's expansionist ambitions. I will continue to cultivate a positive relationship with GER, but will not commit to any alliances against other powers at this time. I will move A SER to RUM, A BOH holds, and F ALB holds.

Greetings, Turkey. I am moving A SER to BUD. I am also moving F ION to GRE. I hope this does not conflict with our agreement. I am open to discussing any adjustments to our plans.

Greetings, Germany. I am moving A SIL to WAR to secure my northern flank. I am also moving A SER to BUD and F ION to GRE. I hope this does not conflict with our agreement. I am open to discussing any adjustments to our plans.

FRA, your continued hostility is noted. However, I reiterate my offer: an alliance against GER in exchange for respecting British naval dominance. Your current course of action will only lead to your demise. Consider this a final opportunity for cooperation.

Apologies for the confusion regarding Bohemia. I am focused on the North. I will not interfere in your Balkan ambitions. I suggest you move A SER to GAL and A SIL to BOH. This will give you a strong position to take VIE.

While we are not eager for conflict, France will not tolerate such blatant disregard for its sovereignty. Withdraw your fleet, and we can discuss a peaceful resolution. Refuse, and face the consequences.

To ITA, France acknowledges your neutrality. However, the Mediterranean is of vital interest to both our nations. France proposes a discussion regarding our respective spheres of influence in the region. Perhaps we can find common ground that benefits us both. What are your thoughts?
